race.comment: Tough contest to end the day. CRESTA RUN (1) is going nicely through her grades with the three wins from her last four starts. Showed good early speed from the wide draw when a commanding on-pace winner over 1100m at Scone. Looks up to this stronger contest from the gate and races best with her runs spaced. BE QUIET (3) handy mare improving with age. Closed strongly from the lengthy break when a courageous fourth over 1100m at Canterbury in BM72 class. Gets a similar set-up today and looms as the main danger. OCEANS ONE (2) tough gelding with a handy record over this track and trip. Gets every chance and looks a key player. CAMPARI TWIST (4) first run for the new yard after a brief let-up. Capable on her day and fitted with a slick trial win over 800m at Gosford. Blinkers come off and sure to be thereabouts.
